FBIS4-16649 "drsov075_b_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Saratov-Moscow Gas Pipeline Blows Up Saratov-Moscow Gas Pipeline Blows Up LD1804130994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1026 GMT 18 Apr 94 LD1804130994 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] On Sunday night, the gas pipeline linking Saratov and Moscow blew up three kilometers east of the city of Lukhovitsy. The Ministry for Emergency Situations told Interfax that the explosion had occurred and a fire flared up as a result of the pipeline break. Gas has been switched off. No one was injured. Consumers are receiving gas from other pipelines. Repair work is underway.
